TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(1,5,1);
$b = random(6,10,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The function \( f(x) = $b x^3 - 3 $b x + $a \)
has two critical numbers.  The smaller one equals \{ans_rule(10) \}
